<span class="header1">CREATIVE PRODUCTION</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need people who are outgoing and
creative.  Here are two examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Managing Editor</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BD/43333.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Managing Editor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A managing editor works in the publishing
industry.  As a managing editor, you would oversee the hiring of
writers and reporters.  You would also plan what is published.  You
would know every aspect of putting together a newspaper or
magazine.  Your job would be important.  But it would be stressful
too.  Managing editors usually have other jobs in publishing before
they are promoted to this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a college degree in English,
literature, or journalism for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of managing editors was $61,370
in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Media Specialist</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BD/43278.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Media Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>To see what a media specialist does, go to your
school media center or library. A media specialist helps others get
ready to give presentations or to chair meetings.  As a media
specialist, you would suggest easy and effective ways to get a
message across.  You would show people how to use the equipment.
You would also see that the equipment was in good repair.  You must
be creative and be comfortable with technology to be good at this
job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A master's degree in library science (MLS) is
necessary for librarian positions in most public, academic, and
special libraries. School librarians do not typically need an MLS
but must meet State licensing requirements. A part-time job at your
local library would give you experience.  You might also volunteer
in your school media center.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of media specialists was
$59,500 in May 2019. </blockquote>

